%20key%20clue%20to%20how%20solar%20storms%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20event%2C%20the%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe%20managed%20to%20capture%20footage%20from%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%20(CMEs)%20ever%20recorded%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.nasa.gov%2Fparkersolarprobe%2F2023%2F09%2F15%2Fparker-observes-powerful-coronal-mass-ejection-vacuum-up-interplanetary-dust%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20could%20help%20us%20better%20understand%20these%20huge%20solar%20explosions%2C%20which%20can%20bring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-storm-earth-northern-southern-lights-auroras-how-to-see-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeautiful%20auroras%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20our%20planet%2C%20but%20also%20wreak%20havoc%20on%20Earth's%20satellites%20and%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20turbulence%20is%20key%20in%20achieving%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20CME%20evolution%20and%20kinematics%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Evangelos%20Paouris%20a%20solar%20physicist%20at%20George%20Mason%20University%20and%20an%20author%20of%20a%20study%20analyzing%20the%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dvidshub.net%2Fvideo%2Fembed%2F916993%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20looked%20at%20footage%20captured%20by%20NASA's%20Parker%20Solar%20probe%20when%20it%20flew%20inside%20a%20coronal%20mass%20ejection%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20this%20footage%2C%20scientists%20spotted%20characteristic%20structures%20called%20Kelvin-Helmholtz%20instabilities%20(KHIs)%20inside%20the%20CME.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKHIs%20are%20structures%20that%20appear%20when%20two%20rapidly%20moving%20fluids%20interact%20with%20each%20other.%20This%20creates%20a%20repeated%20pattern%20of%20swirls%2C%20appearing%20almost%20like%20a%20hand%20drawing%20of%20waves%20on%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Earth%2C%20they%20can%20be%20occasionally%20spotted%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-cloud-formation-virginia-photo-viral-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erare%20fluctus%20clouds%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInside%20CMEs%2C%20they%20are%20slightly%20more%20difficult%20to%20notice.%20That's%20partly%20why%20scientists%20have%20long%20hypothesized%20they%20existed%20inside%20the%20solar%20explosions%20but%20had%20never%20been%20able%20to%20see%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20KHIs%20may%20not%20appear%20to%20many%20of%20us%2C%20scientists%20see%20them%20clearly%20in%20the%202021%20footage%20from%20the%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20never%20anticipated%20that%20KHI%20structures%20could%20develop%20to%20large%20enough%20scales%20to%20be%20imaged%20in%20visible%20light%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Angelos%20Vourlidas%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20information%20can%20help%20scientists%20better%20understand%20how%20the%20CMEs%20propagate%20and%20interact%20with%20solar%20winds%2C%20said%20Paouris.%20And%20that's%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECMEs%20don't%20stay%20confined%20to%20the%20sun.%20When%20they%20explode%2C%20they%20release%20a%20burst%20of%20charged%20particles%20that%20can%20come%20barreling%20through%20space%20to%20hit%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22coronal%20mass%20ejection%20sun%20soho%20nasa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F56eb02aa52bcd01d7b8b6d75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22896%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%202002%20coronal%20mass%20ejection.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3