%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aamc.org%2Fdata-reports%2Freporting-tools%2Freport%2Ftuition-and-student-fees-reports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociation%20of%20American%20Medical%20Colleges%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20finds%20the%20median%20tuition%20for%20first-year%20students%20at%20private%20institutions%20for%20the%202023-2024%20academic%20year%20who%20are%20residents%20was%20%2464%2C000.%20The%20median%20was%20%2465%2C059%20for%20nonresidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20just%20physicians%20that%20could%20see%20a%20shortage%20and%20need%20more%20workers.%20NCHWA%20projections%20show%20registered%20nurses%2C%20dispensing%20opticians%2C%20and%20pharmacists%20are%20other%20types%20of%20healthcare%20workers%20that%20could%20see%20shortages%20through%20the%20next%20several%20years.%20Registered%20nurses%20have%20a%20relatively%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes291141.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%20annual%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20%2481%2C220.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20data%20also%20shows%20the%20need%20for%20healthcare%20professionals.%20LinkedIn%20pointed%20BI%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fbusiness%2Ftalent%2Fblog%2Ftalent-strategy%2Fmost-in-demand-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20in-demand%20jobs%20on%20the%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Care%20specialist%20was%20the%20position%20with%20the%20fastest-growing%20demand%2C%20based%20on%20%26quot%3BRoles%20with%20the%20greatest%20quarter-over-quarter%20increase%20in%20share%20of%20paid%20job%20posts%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202023.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20just%20one%20of%20six%20healthcare-related%20jobs%20part%20of%20the%20top%2010.%20Sonographer%20and%20home%20health%20licensed%20practical%20nurse%20are%20two%20other%20healthcare%20roles%20that%20made%20the%20top%2010%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESign%20language%20interpreter%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221651%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20using%20sign%20language%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660af3f83f923f7dab0328bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221238%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHalfpoint%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESign%20language%20interpreters%20are%20in%20demand.%20Indeed%20data%20compiled%20for%20BI%20finds%20that%20just%20over%2060%25%20of%20sign%20language%20interpreter%20roles%20are%20hard%20to%20fill%2C%20meaning%20they've%20been%20on%20Indeed%20for%2060%20or%20more%20days.%20According%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes273091.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBLS%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20interpreters%20and%20translators%20make%20a%20median%20hourly%20wage%20of%20%2425.79%2C%20and%20a%20median%20annual%20wage%20of%20%2453%2C640.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20National%20Deaf%20Center%20on%20Postsecondary%20Outcomes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationaldeafcenter.org%2Fnews-items%2Fthe-asl-interpreter-shortage-and-its-impact-on-accessibility-in-college-settings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20is%20a%20nationwide%20shortage%20of%20ASL%20interpreters%2C%20even%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20need%20for%20interpreters%20who%20have%20specialized%20skill%20and%20knowledge%20has%20increased%20over%20the%20years%20as%20more%20and%20more%20deaf%20students%20pursue%20medical%20and%20technical%20fields.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETeachers%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221811%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20teacher%20and%20students%20in%20a%20classroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660af49f16bde8d4ead42876%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221358%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Ekali9%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EElementary%20school%20teachers%2C%20high%20school%20teachers%2C%20and%20special%20education%20teachers%20were%20among%20the%20jobs%20with%20the%20most%20postings%20on%20Handshake%20over%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20be%20a%20challenge%20to%20fill%20teacher%20demand%20as%20other%20occupations%20pay%20better%20for%20young%20people.%20ADP's%20chief%20economist%20Nela%20Richardson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-young-teachers-shortage-competitive-pay-schools-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bwages%20might%20discourage%26quot%3B%20young%20people%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20they%20could%20make%20relatively%20more%20or%20see%20their%20salaries%20increase%20faster%20in%20other%20industries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20pay%20for%20%26quot%3BElementary%20School%20Teachers%2C%20Except%20Special%20Education%26quot%3B%20was%20%2461%2C690%20in%202022%2C%20per%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20which%20is%20above%20the%20national%20median%20for%20all%20jobs%2C%20which%20was%20%2446%2C310.%20BLS%20noted%20the%20median%20pay%20for%20%26quot%3BSecondary%20School%20Teachers%2C%20Except%20Special%20and%20Career%2FTechnical%20Education%26quot%3B%20was%20%2462%2C360%2C%20similar%20to%20those%20teaching%20elementary-school%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAccountants%20and%20auditors%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221557%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20talking%20in%20an%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660af5421caec1275a6b6969%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221168%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Barwick%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Handshake%2C%20accountants%20and%20auditors%20were%20two%20of%20the%20roles%20that%20had%20the%20most%20job%20post