20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUBI%20champions%20say%20it%20will%20boost%20the%20economy%20by%20encouraging%20unemployed%20recipients%20to%20take%20jobs%20because%20they%20won't%20lose%20their%20benefits%2C%20and%20provide%20a%20lift%20to%20people's%20mental%20health%20and%20happiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3Bif%20recipients%20were%20to%20spend%20their%20income%20not%20to%20meet%20basic%20needs%2C%20to%20develop%20human%20capital%2C%20or%20to%20save%20for%20the%20future%2C%20wasting%20it%20instead%2C%20this%20would%20be%20a%20worry%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fabian%20Wendt%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20in%20Virginia%20Tech's%20political%20science%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguaranteedincome.us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGuaranteed%20Income%20Pilots%20Dashboard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20joint%20project%20from%20the%20Stanford%20Basic%20Income%20Lab%20and%20the%20Center%20for%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Research%2C%20pulls%20together%20data%20from%20more%20than%2030%20pilot%20programs%20in%20the%20US%20involving%20nearly%208%2C300%20participants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20shows%20that%20about%2036%25%20of%20UBI%20funds%20were%20spent%20on%20retail%20sales%20and%20services%3B%2032%25%20on%20food%20and%20groceries%3B%209%25%20on%20transportation%3B%209%25%20on%20housing%20and%20utilities%3B%206%25%20on%20financial%20transactions%20like%20saving%20and%20investing%3B%204%25%20on%20travel%2C%20leisure%2C%20and%20entertainment%3B%202%25%20on%20healthcare%20and%20medical%20expenses%3B%201.5%25%20on%20miscellaneous%20expenses%3B%20and%200.6%25%20on%20education%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20breakdown%20may%20be%20a%20product%20of%20UBI%20trials%20largely%20focusing%20on%20poorer%20populations%20that%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20use%20the%20money%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20essentials%20and%20pay%20their%20bills%2C%20and%20have%20little%20left%20over%20to%20save%20or%20invest.%20As%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20spending%20on%20health%20and%20education%2C%20that%20might%20reflect%20the%20availability%20of%20government%20programs%20like%20Medicare%20and%20Medicaid%20as%20well%20as%20public%20schooling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20experiments%20have%20turned%20up%20similar%20results%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Hasdell%2C%20a%20research%20advisor%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Basic%20Income%20Lab%2C%20recently%20conducted%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbasicincome.stanford.edu%2Fuploads%2FUmbrella%2520Review%2520BI_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eumbrella%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2016%20studies%20and%20found%20that%20recipients%20spent%20more%20on%20food%20and%20assets%20such%20as%20livestock%20in%20poorer%20countries%2C%20but%20there%20was%20less%20of%20a%20jump%20in%20their%20purchases%20of%20productivity-enhancing%20tools%2C%20and%20a%20mixed%20impact%20on%20savings%20and%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGiveDirectly%2C%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20is%20providing%20universal%20basic%20income%20to%2020%2C000%20people%20across%20200-odd%20royal%20villages%20in%20Kenya%20over%2012%20years.%20Two%20years%20in%2C%20it%20has%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-monthly-cash-payments-nobel-prize-kenya-study-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimproved%20household%20and%20business%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20recipients%20saving%20up%20and%20financing%20bigger%20projects%20via%20banks%20and%20credit%20associations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-antonio-ubi-guaranteed-basic-income-housing-finances-austin-rent-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUpTogether%20gave%20%245%2C200%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%201%2C000%20individuals%20and%20families%20in%20San%20Antonio%2C%20Texas%20over%20a%20period%20of%20about%2025%20months.%20Recipients%20said%20they%20were%20most%20proud%20to%20cover%20their%20bills%2C%20pay%20for%20food%2C%20housing%2C%20and%20transportation%2C%20repay%20debt%20and%20save%2C%20and%20cover%20medical%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Monique%20Gonzalez%20said%20the%20money%20helped%20her%20buy%20shoes%2C%20school%20supplies%2C%20Christmas%20gifts%2C%20and%20enroll%20one%20of%20her%20children%20in%20softball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20participant%2C%20Stephanie%20Hendon%2C%20was%20able%20to%20move%20out%20of%20a%20shelter%20with%20her%20four%20kids%20and%20rent%20a%20three-bedroom%20apartment.%20She%20also%20bought%20a%20new%20car%2C%20new%20clothes%20for%20her%20children%2C%20and%20landed%20a%20new%20job%2C%20setting%20herself%20up%20for%20later%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20spending%20might%20not%20matter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20lower-income%20recipients%20wasting%20their%20UBI%20may%20be%20overblown%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGood%20evidence%20shows%20that%20low-income%20people%20do%20not%20use%20drugs%2C%20alcohol%2C%20or%20tobacco%20at%20a%20greater%20rate%20than%20high-income%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Widerqist%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20depression%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20mental%20illness%20are%20major%20drivers%20of%20drug%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20extent%20that%20UBI%20relieves%20people%20from%20misery%2C%20we%20should%20expect%20it%20would%20decrease%20vice%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20fall%20into%20habits%20of%20bad%20spending%20but%20that%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20where%20their%20income%20is%20coming%20from%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Bruenig%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20a%20think%20tank%20named%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPeople%2527s_Policy_Project%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople's%20Policy%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlenty%20of%20people%20who%20receive%20income%20from%20paychecks%20blow%20it%20on%20drugs%20or%20gambling%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BDoes%20that%20tell%20us%20there%20is%20some%20problem%20with%20our%20program%20of%20paying%20money%20to%20people%20for%20work%3F%20Obviously%20that's%20silly.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20MacKay%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20UNC-Chapel%20Hill%2C%20agreed%20that%20social%20safety%20nets%20shouldn't%20force%20recipients%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Bgood%20choices%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20instead%20show%20them%20respect%20by%20treating%20them%20as%20adults%20capable%20of%20making%20their%20own%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20are%20good%20reasons%20to%20give%20people%20cash%20even%20if%20they%20sometimes%20spend%20it%20in%20ways%20that%20others%20think%20are%20'unwise%2C'%26quot%3B%20MacKay%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-spend-universal-basic-income-ubi-food-housing-transportation-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712138434000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660c318616bde8d4ead4b21b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-spend-universal-basic-income-ubi-food-housing-transportation-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20common%20question%20about%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20or%20UBI%2C%20is%20how%20people%20spend%20the%20money%2C%20but%20early%20trials%20are%20showing%20promising%20results.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmohamed%40insider.com%20(Theron%20Mohamed)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-spend-universal-basic-income-ubi-food-housing-transportation-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Today%2C%20April%203%2C%202024%20%7C%20How%20Much%20Longer%20Until%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-mortgage-refinance-rates-today-wednesday-3-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-we-evaluate-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20have%20increased%20over%20the%20past%20few%20days.%20Average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E30-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20ticked%20up%20above%206.50%25%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20more%20than%20a%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20rates%20to%20go%20down%2C%20inflation%20needs%20to%20cool.%20The%20latest%20Personal%20Consumption%20Expenditures%20price%20index%2C%20which%20is%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20preferred%20measure%20of%20inflation%2C%20showed%20that%20prices%20rose%202.5%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20February%2C%20a%20slight%20uptick%20from%20the%20previous%20month.%20But%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-first-rate-cut-outlook-june-inflation-data-pce-index-2024-3%5C%22%3Eprice%C2%A0increases%20decelerated%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20is%20waiting%20for%20more%20data%20showing%20that%20inflation%20is%20coming%20down%20to%20its%20target%20rate%20of%202%25%20before%20it%20considers%20lowering%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate.%20Once%20the%20Fed%20starts%20cutting%20rates%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20ease.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clevelandfed.org%2Fcollections%2Fspeeches%2F2024%2Fsp-20240402-update-on-us-economy-and-monetary-policy%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Cleveland%20Loretta%20Mester%20reiterated%20the%20need%20for%20more%20data.%20Mester%20noted%20that%20she%20believes%20inflation%20will%20continue%20to%20slow%20but%20that%20the%20path%20to%202%25%20could%20be%20bumpy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20further%20monthly%20readings%20will%20give%20us%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20whether%20the%20disinflation%20process%20is%20stalling%20out%20or%20whether%20the%20start-of-the-year%20readings%20reflect%20a%20temporary%20detour%20on%20the%20downward%20path%20back%20to%20price%20stability%2C%26quot%3B%20Mester%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20expect%20I%20will%20have%20enough%20information%20by%20the%20time%20of%20the%20%5BFederal%20Open%20Market%20Committee's%5D%20next%20meeting%20to%20make%20that%20determination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20next%20meeting%20starts%20on%20April%2030%20and%20wraps%20up%20May%201.%20Investors%20overwhelmingly%20expect%20policy%20makers%20to%20keep%20rates%20steady%20at%20this%20meeting%2C%20but%20are%20currently%20betting%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20will%20cut%20rates%20at%20the%20following%20meeting%20in%20June%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmark