rker%20of%20mine%20has%20a%20whole%20rant%20about%20how%20on%20dating%20apps%20women%20would%20judge%20him%20for%20having%20an%20Android%20(well%2C%20that%20and%20living%20in%20New%20Jersey).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnecdotes%20aside%2C%20this%20form%20of%20supposed%20cyberdiscrimination%20has%20even%20gotten%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%20In%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-antitrust-lawsuit-justice-department-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantitrust%20lawsuit%20against%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleging%20the%20tech%20giant%20has%20unfairly%20cornered%20the%20smartphone%20market%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20explicitly%20calls%20out%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantitrust-doj-lawsuit-apple-green-messages-android-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20green-bubble%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20filing%2C%20it%20says%20people%20without%20Apple%20devices%20often%20feel%20a%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20stigma%2C%20exclusion%2C%20and%20blame%20for%20'breaking'%20chats%20where%20other%20participants%20own%20iPhones.%26quot%3B%20The%20department%20claims%20that's%20on%20purpose%20%E2%80%94%20it%20alleges%20Apple%20takes%20all%20sorts%20of%20measures%20to%20maintain%20a%20monopoly%20on%20smartphones%20and%20keep%20developers%20and%20consumers%20within%20its%20grip%2C%20including%20making%20the%20messaging%20experience%20when%20communicating%20with%20non-iPhone%20users%20different%20and%20weird.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ultimate%20reason%20that%20Apple%20causes%20friction%20with%20products%20it%20doesn't%20make%20is%20clear%3A%20to%20make%20money.%20What%20drives%20consumers%2C%20however%2C%20is%20worth%20pausing%20on.%20Sure%2C%20Apple%20has%20positioned%20the%20iPhone%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bcool%26quot%3B%20phone%2C%20but%20why%20do%20we%20care%3F%20What%20makes%20the%20blue%20iMessage%20bubbles%20the%20preferable%20color%3F%20Why%20do%20so%20many%20consumers%20see%20their%20buying%20habits%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20something%20bigger%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20really%20care%20about%20using%20products%20and%20brands%20to%20express%20who%20they%20are%20to%20themselves%20and%20the%20world%20around%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Nailya%20Ordabayeva%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20business%20administration%20at%20Dartmouth's%20Tuck%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBrands%20that%20have%20a%20really%20well-established%20image%2C%20Apple's%20cool%20image%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20they%20worked%20on%20to%20establish%20over%20the%20years%20%E2%80%94%20consumers%20really%20see%20that%20as%20a%20legitimate%20signal%20of%20their%20own%20coolness%20to%20themselves%20and%20other%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20spent%20more%20than%2015%20years%20fostering%20an%20in-crowd%2Fout-crowd%20scenario%20with%20the%20iPhone.%20The%20Cupertino%2C%20California%2C%20company%20has%20long%20cast%20itself%20as%20hyperinnovative%20and%20alluring%2C%20and%20the%20iPhone%20is%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20those%20efforts.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-steve-jobs-first-iphone-10-years-ago-legendary-keynote-macworld-sale-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20the%20device%20a%20%26quot%3Brevolutionary%20and%20magical%26quot%3B%20product%20when%20he%20introduced%20it%20in%202007%2C%20setting%20the%20tone%20for%20an%20aura%20that%20has%20persisted%20even%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrader-joes-mini-tote-bags-stanley-cups-tiktok-consumerism-marketing-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20other%20trendy%20products%20have%20cycled%20through%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20iPhone%20keeps%20with%20Apple's%20minimalistic%2C%20sleek%20design%20philosophy%20and%20stays%20within%20a%20production%20process%20the%20company%20has%20tight%20control%20over.%20An%20Android%20device%20can%20look%20like%20anything%20and%20be%20from%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20Samsung%2C%20Google%2C%20Motorola.%20There's%20only%20one%20iPhone%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20real%20cheaper%20version%20of%20it%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20reinforces%20the%20design%20allure%20of%20the%20iPhone%20by%20generating%20excitement%20every%20time%20a%20new%20product%20comes%20out.%20Every%20announcement%20of%20a%20new%20iteration%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20small%20the%20changes%20are%2C%20is%20treated%20like%20a%20holy%20event.%20The%20image%20of%20people%20lined%20up%20outside%20the%20Apple%20Store%20on%20the%20day%20of%20an%20iPhone%20launch%20is%20implanted%20in%20our%20collective%20imagination.%20Apple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphones-movies-bad-guys-knives-out-director-rian-johnson-2020-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DJohnson%2520says%2520that%2520while%2520Apple%2Creflects%2520favorably%2522%2520on%2520the%2520company.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon't%20let%20bad%20guys%20in%20movies%20have%20iPhones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lest%20anyone%20get%20the%20wrong%20idea.%20And%20if%20you've%20ever%20watched%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fted-lasso-emotional-intelligence-humility-leadership-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETed%20Lasso%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20or%20anything%20else%20on%20Apple%20TV%2B%2C%20you've%20perhaps%20noticed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-13-notchless-ted-lasso-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPhones%20and%20Apple%20products%20are%20ubiquitous%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20elevating%20the%20iPhone%20to%20the%20status%20of%20a%20prestige%20item%2C%20like%20a%20Louis%20Vuitton%20bag%20or%20a%20Mercedes%20car%2C%20Apple%20can%20play%20on%20consumers'%20desire%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20try%20to%20emulate%20those%20around%20them%20and%20not%20be%20left%20behind.%20People%20have%20a%20tendency%20toward%20conformity%3B%20we%20want%20to%20feel%20like%20we%20belong.%20That's%20especially%20pertinent%20for%20teens%20and%20young%20adults.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20appear%20out%20of%20the%20loop%20or%20of%20lower%20status%2C%20like%20their%20families%20can't%20afford%20a%20higher-priced%20item.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20at%20a%20stage%20where%20they're%20trying%20to%20formulate%20their%20identity%2C%20and%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20formulate%20your%20identity%2C%20you%20also%20figure%20out%20which%20social%20groups%20do%20you%20belong%20to%2C%20in%20which%20are%20you%20an%20insider%20and%20which%20are%20you%20an%20outsider%2C%26quot%3B%20Joseph%20Nunes%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20the%20USC%20Marshall%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20all%20know%20that%20in%20the%20teenage%20years%2C%20being%20an%20insider%2C%20being%20left%20out%2C%20this%20really%20matters%20even%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225145%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Customers%20wait%20in%20line%20to%20buy%20iPhone%2015%20series%20phones%20at%20an%20Apple%20store%20in%20Hangzhou%2C%20East%20China's%20Zhejiang%20province%2C%20Sept%2022%2C%202023.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650d9dc219f33e00190474e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApple%20has%20long%20used%20marketing%20tricks%2C%20like%20endless%20lines%20outside%20its%20stores%2C%20to%20cultivate%20a%20prestige%20image.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20drive%20doesn't%20end%20in%20adulthood%3B%20it%20just%20shifts.%20Maybe%20a%2030-something%20doesn't%20care%20about%20which%20phone%20they%20have%20(though%20many%20still%20do)%2C%20but%20they%20do%20care%20about%20which%20car%20they%20drive%20and%20where%20their%20kids%20go%20to%20school.%20And%20they're%20probably%20still%20holding%20on%20to%20their%20iPhones%2C%20however%20they%20do%20or%20don't%20think%20it%20makes%20them%20look%2C%20because%20they're%20used%20to%20them.%20They're%20already%20in%20too%20deep%2C%20and%20the%20switching%20cost%20feels%20too%20high%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20all%20their%20other%20devices%20are%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHumans%20are%20a%20hierarchical%20species.%20We%20look%20down%20to%20feel%20better%20about%20ourselves%20and%20look%20up%20to%20gauge%20where%20we%20stand%20on%20the%20scale.%20People%20seek%20ways%20to%20signal%20status%20in%20that%20social%20comparison%20setting%2C%20and%20having%20a%20supposedly%20attractive%20or%20special%20thing%20is%20a%20way%20to%20accomplish%20that.%20It's%20a%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bconspicuous%20consumption%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20way%20to%20display%20your%20standing%20and%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20who%20seek%20approval%20of%20others%20or%20are%20motivated%20by%20social%20dominance%20engage%20in%20conspicuous%20consumption%20to%20showcase%20their%20elitism%20to%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20Joshua%20Clarkson%2C%20a%20consumer%20psychologist%20and%20marketing%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cincinnati%2C%20told%20me%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20imagine%20both%20of%20these%20groups%20of%20consumers%20being%20heavily%20vested%20in%20iMessage%20(i.e.%2C%20to%20not%20be%20the%20person%20with%20the%20Android%20on%20the%20group%20chat)%20as%20either%20a%20way%20to%20fit%20in%20(if%20seeking%20others'%20approval)%20or%20a%20way%20to%20exclude%20others%20(if%20driven%20by%20social%20dominance).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20brands%20are%20good%20at%20playing%20into%20these%20predispositions.%20Luxury%20and%20prestige%20companies%20say%20their%20products%20are%20of%20higher%20quality%2C%20which%20is%20often%20true.%20But%20the%20functional%20attributes%20are%20reinforced%20by%20aspirational%20positioning%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20just%20make%20something%20of%20a%20higher%20quality%3B%20you%20have%20to%20make%20people%20think%20it's%20worth%20more.%20That%20positioning%20allows%20companies%20to%20price%20their%20premium-perceived%20products%20accordingly.%20They%20advertise%20them%20with%20influencers%20and%20celebrities%20who%20align%20with%20their%20image.%20They%20often%20inject%20a%20sense%20of%20scarcity%20and%20urgency%20into%20the%20mix.%20While%20iPhones%20are%20ubiquitous%2C%20the%20latest%20versions%2C%20which%20also%20come%20with%20a%20new%20price%20point%2C%20are%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20societal%20context%20matters%20here%2C%20too%2C%20Nunes%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20a%20period%20of%20society%20today%20that's%20got%20great%20inequality.%20And%20then%20that%20sort%20of%20reinforces%20this%20notion%20that%20there%20are%20the%20haves%20and%20the%20have-nots.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20wanting%20an%20iPhone.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20some%20people%20are%20constantly%20seeking%20out%20prestige%20and%20status%20through%20their%20consumption%2C%20it%20would%20be%20stranger%20if%20there%20weren't%20some%20drive%20to%20have%20whichever%20phone%20is%20perceived%20as%20the%20best.%20And%20consumers%20are%20clearly%20picking%20up%20what%20Apple%20is%20putting%20down%20%E2%80%94%20at%20a%20nearly%20%243%20trillion%20market%20cap%2C%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20most%20valuable%20companies%20in%20the%20world.%20But%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20having%20whatever%20the%20fancy%20thing%20is%2C%20ultimately%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaterialism-eroding-happiness-2014-8%23while-we-regard-an-increase-in-consumer-spending-as-a-good-thing-for-the-economy-its-not-such-great-news-for-the-environment-or-for-our-individual-levels-of-satisfaction-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoesn't%20make%20us%20happier%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sometimes%2C%20it%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarlsonschool.umn.edu%2Fnews%2Fluxury-products-change-behavior-and-not-good-way%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emakes%20us%20more%20judgmental%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hence%20the%20whole%20green-bubble%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20see%20the%20things%20we%20have%20as%20an%20extension%20of%20ourselves%2C%20perhaps%20especially%20our%20phones%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20where%20many%20people%20live%20a%20lot%20of%20their%20lives.%20iPhone%20bias%20probably%20isn't%20going%20anywhere%2C%20even%20if%20we're%20unaware%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrands%20are%20more%20than%20just%20the%20functional%20products%20that%20they%20offer%2C%20that%20they%20are%20this%20symbol%20of%20who%20consumers%20want%20to%20see%20themselves%20as%20and%20who%20they%20want%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Ordabayeva%20said.%20Apparently%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20want%20to%20see%20ourselves%20as%20iPhone%20users%20and%20all%20that%20comes%20with%20it.%20I%20switched%20from%20a%20Samsung%20to%20an%20iPhone%20in%202014.%20It%20just%20seemed%20like%20the%20thing%20to%20do%2C%20which%20is%20what%20Apple%20is%20banking%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-doj-lawsuit-antitrust-green-bubble-samsung-stigma-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712136422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660c370316bde8d4ead4bb3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-doj-lawsuit-antitrust-green-bubble-samsung-stigma-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apple%20uses%20consumer%20psychology%20to%20make%20it%20feel%20like%20the%20%26quot%3Bcool%26quot%3B%20brand%2C%20which%20the%20DOJ%20says%20created%20a%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20stigma%26quot%3B%20toward%20non-iPho