rset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660489c01caec1275a6a1feb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECaiaimage%2FChris%20Ryan%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20colleges%20that%20were%20test-optional%20during%20the%20pandemic%20are%20requiring%20SAT%20or%20ACT%20scores%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThose%20schools%20have%20said%20that%20having%20scores%20will%20help%20them%20recruit%20a%20more%20diverse%20student%20body.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20colleges%20in%20the%20country%20are%20remaining%20test-optional.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20colleges%20are%20bringing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstandardized-testing-poses-health-risks-and-causes-students-stress-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estandardized%20testing%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20to%20their%20admissions%20processes%20after%20nixing%20them%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they're%20still%20not%20in%20the%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20some%20prestigious%20schools%20announced%20they%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdartmouth-brings-back-sat-act-standardized-test-requirement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonce%20again%20require%20SAT%20or%20ACT%20scores%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20prospective%20students'%20applications.%20Dartmouth%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadmissions.dartmouth.edu%2Fapply%2Fupdate-testing-policy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20that%20while%20it%20took%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Btest-optional%26quot%3B%20policy%20in%20response%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20will%20be%20reinstating%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-drops-sat-act-scores-admission-requirement-until-2026-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etesting%20requirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20class%20of%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20bottom%20line%20is%20simple%3A%20we%20believe%20a%20standardized%20testing%20requirement%20will%20improve%E2%80%94not%20detract%20from%E2%80%94our%20ability%20to%20bring%20the%20most%20promising%20and%20diverse%20students%20to%20our%20campus%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20university%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadmissions.yale.edu%2Ftest-flexible%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYale%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brown.edu%2Fnews%2F2024-03-05%2Fadmissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrown%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20similar%20announcements%2C%20saying%20they%20conducted%20studies%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20found%20requiring%20testing%20allowed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethem%20to%20attract%20the%20most%20diverse%20student%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20analysis%20made%20clear%20that%20SAT%20and%20ACT%20scores%20are%20among%20the%20key%20indicators%20that%20help%20predict%20a%20student's%20ability%20to%20succeed%20and%20thrive%20in%20Brown's%20demanding%20academic%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown's%20Provost%20Francis%20Doyle%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20these%20elite%20schools%20are%20still%20outnumbered%20by%20the%20colleges%20that%20decided%20standardized%20testing%20stood%20in%20the%20way%20of%20otherwise-qualified%20applicants.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffairtest.org%2Foverwhelming-majority-of-u-s-colleges-and-universities-remain-act-sat-optional-or-test-blind-score-free-for-fall-2025%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Fair%20and%20Open%20Testing%2C%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20colleges%20will%20be%20test-optional%20for%20fall%202025%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTest-optional%20policies%20continue%20to%20dominate%20at%20national%20universities%2C%20state%20flagships%2C%20and%20selective%20liberal%20arts%20colleges%20because%20they%20typically%20result%20in%20more%20applicants%2C%20academically%20stronger%20applicants%20and%20more%20diversity%2C%26quot%3B%20FairTest%20Executive%20Director%20Harry%20Feder%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20surrounding%20standardized%20testing%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhechingerreport.org%2Fstandardized-tests-in-their-current-format-are-incredibly-antiquated%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-debated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20some%20argue%20the%20tests%20can%20put%20lower-income%20students%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20because%20they%20might%20not%20have%20access%20to%20the%20same%20tutoring%20resources%20that%20wealthier%20students%20have%2C%20others%20argue%20the%20tests%20give%20students%20from%20all%20backgrounds%20a%20way%20to%20show%20their%20skills%20%E2%80%94%20and%20give%20schools%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20choose%20who%20they%20should%20admit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDominique%20Baker%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Delaware%20who%20researches%20education%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20primarily%20financial%20aid%20and%20admissions%20policies%20%E2%80%94%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20schools%20that%20are%20reinstating%20testing%20requirements%20right%20now%20didn't%20choose%20to%20go%20test-optional%20because%20they%20thought%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20policy%20decision.%26quot%3B%20The%20pandemic%20forced%20them%20to%20do%20so%20because%20students%20couldn't%20get%20to%20testing%20sites%2C%20and%20that's%20no%20longer%20an%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20institutions%20we're%20currently%20talking%20about%2C%20they're%20requiring%20tests%20again%20and%20didn't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20ever%20stop%20requiring%20tests%2C%26quot%3B%20Baker%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20students%20should%20know%20about%20the%20schools%20changing%20their%20policies%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20it%20could%20mean%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20return%20of%20some%20testing%20requirements%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20of%20the%20Ivy%20League%20schools%20that%20are%20reinstating%20testing%20requirements%20cited%20their%20aim%20to%20help%20broaden%20diversity%20on%20campus%2C%20some%20other%20schools%20have%20put%20forth%20slightly%20different%20reasons%20for%20their%20shift%20in%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Texas-Austin%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.utexas.edu%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Fut-austin-reinstates-standardized-test-scores-in-admissions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20reinstatement%20of%20testing%20requirements%20in%20March%20after%20shifting%20to%20test-optional%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Its%20reason%3A%20requiring%20testing%20scores%20would%20help%20the%20school%20choose%20between%20many%20high%20school%20seniors%20with%20high%20GPAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20experience%20during%20the%20test-optional%20period%20reinforced%20that%20standardized%20testing%20is%20a%20valuable%20tool%20for%20deciding%20who%20is%20admitted%C2%A0and%C2%A0making%20sure%20those%20students%20are%20placed%20in%20majors%20that%20are%20the%20best%20fit%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20university's%20president%20Jay%20Hartzell%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAlso%2C%C2%A0with%20an%20abundance%20of%C2%A0high%20school%20GPAs%20surrounding%204.0%2C%20especially%20among%20our%20auto-admits%2C%C2%A0an%C2%A0SAT%20or%20ACT%20score%20is%20a%20proven%20differentiator%20that%20is%20in%20each%20student's%20and%20the%20University's%20best%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20other%20schools%20that%20adopted%20test-optional%20during%20the%20pandemic%20have%20chosen%20to%20maintain%20the%20practice.%20The%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frecord.umich.edu%2Farticles%2Fu-m-formally-adopts-test-optional-admissions-policy%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520University%2520of%2520Michigan%2520has%2Cas%2520part%2520of%2520their%2520application.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20that%20it%20would%20be%20formally%20adopting%20a%20test-optional%20admissions%20policy.%20It%20said%20that%20since%20the%20fall%20of%202020%2C%20the%20school%20saw%20%26quot%3Ba%20significant%20increase%20in%20applications%20from%20students%20from%20all%20backgrounds%2C%26quot%3B%20suggesting%20that%20a%20test-optional%20policy%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20a%20more%20diverse%20student%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20it%20means%20for%20schools%20and%20students%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20some%20schools%20have%20wanted%20to%20maintain%20test%20score%20requirements%2C%20Baker%20said%2C%20is%20because%20of%20their%20link%20to%20financial%20aid.%20While%20some%20financial%20aid%20is%20need-based%20%E2%80%94%20or%20based%20on%20a%20student%20or%20family's%20income%20level%20%E2%80%94%20a%20college%20can%20choose%20to%20award%20aid%20based%20on%20merit%2C%20which%20it%20evaluates%20using%20a%20student's%20GPA%20or%20test%20scores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrequently%2C%20the%20most%20generous%20state%20financial%20aid%20that%20those%20states%20offer%20require%20test%20scores.%20And%20so%20what%20the%20state%20could%20do%20is%20they%20could%20say%2C%20'We%20did%20a%20really%20short%20pause%2C%20but%20now%20we're%20going%20back%20to%20requiring%20test%20scores%20for%20these%20financial%20aid%20pieces%2C'%26quot%3B%20Baker%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20state%20legislatures%20could%20also%20encourage%20institutions%20to%20go%20back%20to%20requiring%20tests.%20So%20I%20also%20think%20that%20there%20is%20a%20role%20that%20politics%20plays%20within%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20wide%20range%20of%20testing%20policies%20can%20be%20confusing%20for%20students.%20For%20many%20schools%2C%20the%20two%20test-optional%20and%20testing-required%20categories%20are%20just%20umbrellas%20%E2%80%94%20there%20can%20be%20different%20policies%20within%20each%20college%2C%20like%20requiring%20tests%20for%20an%20honors%20program%20but%20not%20for%20regular%20admission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20data%20has%20shown%20students%20have%20continued%20to%20take%20tests%20despite%20applying%20to%20schools%20with%20test-optional%20policies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.collegeboard.org%2Fsat-program-results-class-2023-show-continued-growth-sat-participation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20College%20Board%2C%201.9%20million%20students%20in%20the%20high%20school%20class%20of%202023%20took%20the%20SAT%20at%20least%20once%2C%20an%20increase%20from%201.7%20million%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20forward%2C%20Baker%20said%20it's%20important%20that%20if%20more%20schools%20choose%20to%20switch%20their%20testing%20policies%2C%20they%20consider%20the%20announcement's%20timing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20times%20you%20take%20the%20test%2C%20the%20better%20your%20score%20is.%20So%20if%20an%20institution%20announces%20in%20February%20or%20March%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20requiring%20tests%20for%20the%20fall%2C%20then%20students%20really%20do%20not%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20time%20to%20take%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Baker%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20do%20think%20that%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20announcement%20and%20the%20timing%20of%20when%20the%20policy%20takes%20effect%20really%2C%20really%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-colleges-require-standardized-testing-sat-admissions-what-it-means-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712136302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660489cc3f923f7dab01e31e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-colleges-require-standardized-testing-sat-admissions-what-it-means-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20colleges%20are%20starting%20to%20bring%20back%20standardized%20testing%20requirements%20for%20applicants.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-colleges-require-standardized-testing-sat-admissions-what-it-means-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BOmar%20Abdullah%20Left%20No%20Option%26quot%3B%3A%20PDP's%20Solo%20Fight%20Plan%20Fresh%20Blow%20To%20INDIA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWeeks%20ahead%20of%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20joined%20the%20list%20of%20states%20where%20INDIA%20allies%20are%20contesting%20against%20each%20other.%20The%20Mehbooba%20Mufti-led%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%20has%20decided%20to%20go%20solo%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnnouncing%20the%20decision%20at%20a%20press%20meet%2C%20Ms%20Mufti%20said%20her%20party%20will%20contest%20the%20three%20seats%20in%20Kashmir%20Valley%20and%20will%20soon%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20contesting%20the%20two%20parliamentary%20seats%20in%20Jammu.%C2%A0She%20also%20hit%20out%20at%20ally%20National%20Conference%20for%20its%20%26quot%3Bunilateral%26quot%3B%20decision%20to%20contest%20all%20seats%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20comes%20after%20National%20Conference%20announced%20that%20it%20will%20contest%20all%20three%20seats%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20named%20Mian%20Altaf%20as%20its%20candidate%20from%20Anantnag-Rajouri%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHitting%20out%20at%20National%20Conference%20and%20its%20leader%20Omar%20Abdullah%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20National%20Conference%20and%20Omar%20Abdullah%20didn't%20leave%20any%20option%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20was%20for%20political%20parties%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20remain%20united.%20But%20the%20attitude%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%20leadership%20was%20hurtful%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20INDI%20alliance's%20meeting%20took%20place%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20I%20said%20there%20that%20since%20(NC%20president)%20Farooq%20Abdullah%20is%20our%20senior%20leader%2C%20he%20will%20take%20a%20decision%20(on%20seat%20sharing)%20and%20will%20do%20justice.%20I%20had%20hoped%20he%20would%20keep%20the%20party%20interests%20aside%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20the%20National%20Conference%20decided%20to%20contest%20all%20three%20seats%20in%20Kashmir%20unilaterally%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Mufti%20said%20that%20if%20the%20National%20Conference%20had%20consulted%20the%20PDP%20before%20announcing%20the%20decision%2C%20her%20party%20could%20have%20decided%20not%20to%20field%20candidates%20in%20the%20larger%20interest%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20had%20to%20take%20the%20same%20decision%2C%20if%20they%20thought%20that%20they%20had%20a%20better%20voice%20than%20the%20PDP%20to%20raise%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20then%20they%20should%20have%20told%20me%20two%20months%20ago%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20contest%20themselves%20and%20told%20me%20not%20to%20field%20candidates%2C%20then%20perhaps%2C%20for%20the%20larger%20interest%2C%20we%20would%20not%20have%20contested%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%2C%20the%20way%20Omar%20(Abdullah)%20announced%20the%20decision%20without%20taking%20us%20into%20confidence%2C%20it%20hurt%20my%20workers%20and%20broke%20their%20hearts%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Conference%20last%20month%20announced%20that%20it%20will%20be%20contesting%20all%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20the%20valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20meet%20yesterday%2C%20Omar%20Abdullah%20had%20slammed%20the%20media%20for%20trying%20to%20create%20a%20rift%20between%20National%20Conference%20and%20PDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20you%20making%20the%20PDP%20fight%20us%3F%20Has%20the%20PDP%20said%20anywhere%20that%20they%20will%20contest%20elections%3F%20It%20is%20you%20people%20who%20are%20fuelling%20this.%20I%20heard%20the%20speech%20of%20Mehboba%20Mufti%20in%20Delhi%2C%20she%20said%20Farooq%20sahib%20and%20we%20are%20together%20and%20we%20will%20not%20break%20the%20INDIA%20alliance.%20Why%20are%20you%20trying%20to%20make%20us%20fight%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20National%20Conference's%20decision%20to%20contest%20all%20three%20seats%20in%20Kashmir%20was%20based%20on%20who%20won%20the%20previous%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20puts%20the%20Congress%20in%20a%20tricky%20spot.%20Now%20it%20must%20decide%20whether%20it%20will%20support%20the%20PDP%20or%20National%20Conference.%20The%20PDP's%20decision%20will%20also%20add%20a%20punch%20to%20the%20BJP's%20campaign%20against%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20over%20the%20bloc's%20members%20taking%20each%20other%20on%20in%20multiple%20states%2C%20including%20Kerala%2C%20Punjab%20and%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712136300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Ffhip29vg_mehbooba-mufti-omar-abdullah-split_625x300_03_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fomar-abdullah-mehbooba-mufti-omar-abdullah-left-no-option-pdps-solo-fight-plan-fresh-blow-to-india-5365927%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Weeks%20ahead%20of%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20joined%20the%20list%20of%20states%20where%20INDIA%20allies%20are%20contesting%20against%20each%20other.%20The%20Mehbooba%20Mufti-led%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%20has%20decided%20to%20go%20solo%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%22%2C%22author%